				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$J\left( {{\rm GeneSet_ A},{\rm GeneSet_B}} \right) = \frac{{\left| {{\rm GeneSet_A}\mathop { \cap }\nolimits {\rm GeneSet_ B}} \right|}}{{\left| {{\rm GeneSet_A\mathop { \cup }\nolimits GeneSet_B}} \right|}}$$\end{document}JGeneSetA,GeneSetB=GeneSetA ∩GeneSetBGeneSetA ∪GeneSetBThe index ranges between 0 and 1, where 0 would indicate no similarity and 1 would indicate that the two lists are identical.
